For getting numerical input from a User, I prefer using the [Scanner.nextLine()](https://www.tutorialspoint.com/java/util/scanner_nextline.htm) method in conjunction with the [String.matches()](https://www.tutorialspoint.com/java/java_string_matches.htm) method and a simple [Regular Expression](https://www.vogella.com/tutorials/JavaRegularExpressions/article.html) ([&quot;\\\d+&quot;](https://www.vogella.com/tutorials/JavaRegularExpressions/article.html#meta-characters)). You don&#39;t need to trap an exception this way. I just find it more flexible.

